            . I am one of the clerks of Maberley. I assisted in searching the <rs id="t18131027-32-deflabel187" type="occupation">cutter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18131027-32-defend366 t18131027-32-deflabel187"></join>s. Mr.<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181310270028"></xptr>Edwards caught hold of the prisoner's waist. I caught hold of his collar. I drew from under his waistcoat this piece of blue cloth; there is rather better than a yard of it, and there is the broad arrow upon it.</p>
               <p>MR. STEVENS. The prisoner was a cutter in Mr. Maberley's employ. The cloth is the property of 
